/-!
# String Case Conversion
This module implements conversion of lowercase letters to uppercase in a string.

Edge cases:
- Empty string returns empty string
- Non-alphabetic characters remain unchanged
-/

def toUpperCase (s : String) : String :=
  s.map fun c => c.toUpper

/-!
# Unit Tests
-/

/-- Basic test case -/
example : toUpperCase "hello" = "HELLO" := by native_decide
#eval toUpperCase "hello" -- expected: "HELLO"

/-- Empty string test case -/
example : toUpperCase "" = "" := by native_decide
#eval toUpperCase "" -- expected: ""

/-- Mixed case and non-alphabetic characters test -/
example : toUpperCase "Hello, World! 123" = "HELLO, WORLD! 123" := by native_decide
#eval toUpperCase "Hello, World! 123" -- expected: "HELLO, WORLD! 123"

/-!
# Properties
-/

/-- Idempotence property: applying toUpperCase twice is same as once -/
def idempotence_prop (s : String) : Prop :=
  toUpperCase (toUpperCase s) = toUpperCase s

/-- Empty string property: empty string remains empty -/
def empty_string_prop : Prop :=
  toUpperCase "" = ""

/-- Length preservation property: output string has same length as input -/
def length_preservation_prop (s : String) : Prop :=
  (toUpperCase s).length = s.length

/-!
# Theorems
-/

/-- Idempotence theorem -/
theorem idempotence_thm (s : String) : idempotence_prop s := sorry

/-- Empty string theorem -/
theorem empty_string_thm : empty_string_prop := sorry

/-- Length preservation theorem -/
theorem length_preservation_thm (s : String) : length_preservation_prop s := sorry

/-!
# String Case Conversion
This module implements conversion of lowercase letters to uppercase in a string.

Edge cases:
- Empty string returns empty string
- Non-alphabetic characters remain unchanged
-/

def toUpperCase (s : String) : String :=
  s.map fun c => c.toUpper

/-!
# Unit Tests
-/

/-- Basic test case -/
example : toUpperCase "hello" = "HELLO" := by native_decide
#eval toUpperCase "hello" -- expected: "HELLO"

/-- Empty string test case -/
example : toUpperCase "" = "" := by native_decide
#eval toUpperCase "" -- expected: ""

/-- Mixed case and non-alphabetic characters test -/
example : toUpperCase "Hello, World! 123" = "HELLO, WORLD! 123" := by native_decide
#eval toUpperCase "Hello, World! 123" -- expected: "HELLO, WORLD! 123"

/-!
# Properties
-/

/-- Idempotence property: applying toUpperCase twice is same as once -/
def idempotence_prop (s : String) : Prop :=
  toUpperCase (toUpperCase s) = toUpperCase s

/-- Empty string property: empty string remains empty -/
def empty_string_prop : Prop :=
  toUpperCase "" = ""

/-- Length preservation property: output string has same length as input -/
def length_preservation_prop (s : String) : Prop :=
  (toUpperCase s).length = s.length

/-!
# Theorems
-/

/-- Idempotence theorem -/
theorem idempotence_thm (s : String) : idempotence_prop s := sorry

/-- Empty string theorem -/
theorem empty_string_thm : empty_string_prop := sorry
